fields
data.description: uid, name, state, activityState, lastCommDate, commStatus, gateway, subscriptions, labels, applications, metadata, communication, data, heartbeat, statusReport, reports, lastSyncDate, syncStatus

Returns a paginated list of systems with their complete details.  It is possible to restrain the result list using criteria parameters.  Returned systems are shown only with the following attributes uid, name, state, type, activityState, lastCommDate, commStatus, lastSyncDate, syncStatus To display more or less attributes, the fields parameter has to be set. Though system creation date is not publicly exposed, the default sort order is based on the creation date. More information about paging, filtering, and sorting here

data.name: Find Systems

data.description: Get a temporal aggregation of data points for the system matching the unique identifier and the data id defined in the url. Most recent datapoints are returned first. Three months of data are available.
data.name: Historical aggregated datapoints

data.description: Get the historical values of a raw data for the system matching the unique identifier and the data id defined in the url. Most recent datapoints are returned first.  Limitations:  3 months 10000 values which means you cannot access a value older than 3 months or after the first 10000 values.
data.name: Historical raw datapoints

data.description: Install or upgrade an application on a set of systems defined by a label or a list of uids.
data.name: Install Application

data.description: Get the last datapoints of the system matching the unique identifier of data defined in the url. If no data identifier is set, the last datapoint for all data will be retrieved.
data.name: Last datapoints

data.description: Retrieve the list of past messages. The uid, timestamp, protocol and datapoints count are retrieved. Duplicate data are counted.
data.name: List of messages
